name: Zoo Flask print
description:
Sister Arrow is an artist and illustrator inspired by nature, metaphysics and primitive life. Zoo Flask is part of her 'vessel' series, inspired by a love on terrariums and plantlife.

• Signed by the arist
• New 5 colour re-edition
• A4 Risograph print on 200gsm stock

name: Monika Monster Future First Woman on Mars
description: Monika is a 22 year-old student from Poland studying math, science and astronomy in New York City. Valerie Phillips is a renowned London-based photographer who spent a few years (on and off) documenting Monica's life studying, swimming, eating doughnuts, partying and just walking around. signed by the author, this unique book is printed on lovely matte stock with great commentary from Valerie and Monika about each other

name: Birdball
description:
A simple ceramic birdhouse inspired by the natural forms of bird nests, Birdball provides functional nesting for small garden visitors like blue tits, coal tits and marsh tits. The hole is large enough to allow them in, but small enough to keep out predators. 

• Made in Devon, each Birdball is supplied with stainless steel wire (1m long), a tree protector and detailed instructions.

name: Vintage Science Textbook Envelopes
description:
Handmade by the crafty folks over at Present&Correct, each one-of-a-kind envelope is made using 1960s and 70s science textbooks and features a blank card inside and an address label on the front. Ideal for invites, thank-yous and other essential correspondence of a scientific nature.

• Each pack contains 5 envelopes and 5 blank note cards.
• No two envelopes are alike
